public class XsTOpenAttrsImpl
extends XsObjectImpl
implements XsTOpenAttrs

A common base type for most of the schema elements. Implements the following specification: 

  <xs:complexType name="openAttrs">
    <xs:annotation>
      <xs:documentation>
        This type is extended by almost all schema types
        to allow attributes from other namespaces to be
        added to user schemas.
      </xs:documentation>
    </xs:annotation>
    <xs:complexContent>
      <xs:restriction base="xs:anyType">
        <xs:anyAttribute namespace="##other" processContents="lax"/>
      </xs:restriction>
    </xs:complexContent>
  </xs:complexType>

Author:
Jochen Wiedmann

public org.xml.sax.Attributes getOpenAttributes()
Description copied from interface: XsTOpenAttrs

Returns the attributes having other namespaces.

Specified by:
getOpenAttributes in interface XsTOpenAttrs

setAttribute

public boolean setAttribute(java.lang.String pQName,
                            java.lang.String pNamespaceURI,
                            java.lang.String pLocalName,
                            java.lang.String pValue)
                     throws org.xml.sax.SAXException

This method receives all the attributes, including those from the XML schema namespace. The method refuses to handle the attribute, if it has the XML schema namespace by returning the value false. Otherwise, the attribute is added to the list returned by getOpenAttributes() and the value true is returned.

Throws:
org.xml.sax.SAXException
